I have a dynatable that converts a potentially quite large table. I thought it would be nice to have a loading image show while it is processing.

I found the docs [here](https://www.dynatable.com/#processing-indicator) but can&#39;t seem to get it to work. Interestingly, they say that it should do a simple version of this by default but I can&#39;t see any evidence of that happening.

Here&#39;s a simplification of the code I&#39;m using:

    $(document).ready(function() {
      // Initialise the dynatable on the data from query.
      $(&#39;#my-table&#39;).dynatable({
          inputs: {
              processingText: &#39;Loading...&#39;
          },
          features: {
            perPageSelect: false
          },
          dataset: {
              perPageDefault: 50,
          }
      }).bind(&#39;dynatable:afterProcess&#39;, initialiseTable);
    });

the `initialiseTable` function just applies some css classes and adds even listeners.

I&#39;ve tried a couple of different aproaches:

1. I&#39;ve tried assigning the table to a variable:

   `var mytable = $(&#39;#my-table&#39;).dynatable({...` 

    and then calling 

   `mytable.processingIndicator.show()` but this didn&#39;t work.


2. I&#39;ve also tried binding it to a beforeProcess (and init) even hook directly:

        $(&#39;#my-table&#39;).dynatable({ ... })
        .bind(&#39;dynatable:beforeProcess&#39;, processingIndicator.show() )
        .bind(&#39;dynatable:afterProcess&#39;, initialiseTable);

    I&#39;ve tried to call `processingIndicator.show()` both with and without `this` but in all cases I get an `Uncaught ReferenceError: processingIndicator is not defined`

I checked [this post](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/46456225/dynatable-features-is-undefined) but there isn&#39;t any `settings` property I can see when I output the contents of `mytable`.

Has anybody managed to get this feature to work and if so how?

Many Thanks.

